  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into thin chips</p><p>Add the <strong>chips</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1578321057017-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1578321057017-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1578321057017-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1578321057017-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1578321057017-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chips are cooking, trim, then slice your<strong> spring onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1578321061902-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1578321061902-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1578321061902-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1578321061902-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1578321061902-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>beef mince</strong>, <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>sliced spring onion</strong>, <strong>soy sauce </strong>and <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> to a bowl with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and a grind of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Using clean hands, give everything a very good mix up until fully combined – this is your <strong>burger mixture</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1578321068318-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1578321068318-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1578321068318-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1578321068318-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1578321068318-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Divide the <strong>burger mixture</strong> and shape into 1 patty per person</p><p>Sprinkle your <strong>toasted sesame seeds</strong> evenly over the burger patty[ies] – this is your <strong>sesame beef patty[ies]</strong></p><p>Lightly oil a baking tray with <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and add the <strong>sesame beef patty[ies]</strong>,<strong> </strong>then<strong> </strong>put the tray in the oven for 15-20 min or until cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1578321072465-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1578321072465-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1578321072465-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1578321072465-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1578321072465-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine <strong>half </strong>of your <strong>sriracha </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), with your <strong>rice vinegar</strong> and a pinch of <strong>sugar </strong>and <strong>salt </strong>in a bowl – this is your<strong> pickling liquid</strong></p><p>Top, tail, peel and grate your <strong>carrot[s]</strong>, then peel lengths off your <strong>cucumber</strong> until you end up with a pile of <strong>cucumber ribbons</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>grated carrot </strong>and <strong>cucumber ribbons </strong>to the bowl, give everything a good mix up and set aside – this is your <strong>quick-pickled slaw</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1578321077685-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1578321077685-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1578321077685-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1578321077685-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1578321077685-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>brioche bun[s]</strong> in half</p><p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat, and once hot, add the <strong>brioche halves</strong> cut-side down, and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted and charred</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? You might need to do this in batches!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1578321083660-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1578321083660-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1578321083660-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1578321083660-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1578321083660-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>mayo</strong> and <strong>remaining sriracha</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) in a bowl – this is your<strong> sriracha mayo</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> roughly, including the stalks</p><p>Drain the <strong>quick-pickled slaw</strong> of any excess pickling liquid and discard the liquid</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1578321087968-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1578321087968-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1578321087968-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1578321087968-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1578321087968-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To assemble, spread the <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>brioche base </strong>with some of the <strong>sriracha mayo</strong>, then top with a <strong>sesame beef patty</strong>, some<strong> quick-pickled slaw</strong>, another dollop of <strong>sriracha mayo </strong>and<strong> </strong>the <strong>toasted brioche lid </strong>– this is your<strong> sesame beef burger</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>chips</strong> and any <strong>remaining quick-pickled slaw</strong> to the side</p><p>Sprinkle the <strong>chopped coriander </strong>over the quick-pickled slaw</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
